caption.p: Mean average luminescence, represented as relative light units adjusted for protein concentration, measured after lysis of cells incubated with solvent-exposed MVA ( A) or Ad ( B). Welch’s ANOVA and Games–Howell’s post-hoc tests were used to make statistical comparisons. A p-value of less than 0.05 was considered statistically significant and indicated by an asterisk. Error bars represent the standard deviation, n = 3.
